.TH "xas_split" 9 "xas_split" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xas_split \- Split a multi-index entry into smaller entries.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xas_split
.BI "(struct xa_state *xas "  ","
.BI "void *entry "  ","
.BI "unsigned int order "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xas" 12
XArray operation state.
.IP "entry" 12
New entry to store in the array.
.IP "order" 12
Current entry order.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The size of the new entries is set in \fIxas\fP.  The value in \fIentry\fP is
copied to all the replacement entries.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Any context.  The caller should hold the xa_lock.
